Description: Limestone ostracon: inscribed on both sides (top recto is bottom verso). On the recto five lines, and on the verso three lines (incomplete and almost completely washed off) of unknown literary texts (hymns?), with red verse points.
Curator's comments: On the acquisition see: B. Muhs and T. Vorderstrasse,' Collectiing Egyptian Antiquities in the year 1838: Reverend William Hodge Mill and Robert Curzon, Baron Zouche', Journal of Egyptian Archaeology (2008), pp. 223-245.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (389700) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/389700)
